## 1. Purpose

These rules define how the cursor should behave across the project for a consistent and accessible user experience.

## 2. General Cursor Style

- Default cursor for all elements: `cursor: default`
- Interactive elements (buttons, links, clickable cards): `cursor: pointer`
- Disabled elements: `cursor: not-allowed`
- Text input or editable area: `cursor: text`

## 3. Custom Cursor (Optional)

If a design later requires a custom cursor:

- Implement it as a small reusable module under `/scripts/cursor/`
- Avoid using large libraries; only lightweight TS logic
- Styles must remain accessible and not hide the native cursor on touch devices

## 4. Tailwind Integration

When using TailwindCSS v4:

```html
<button class="cursor-pointer">Click me</button>
<p class="cursor-text">Editable area</p>
<div class="cursor-not-allowed opacity-50">Disabled</div>
```
